						<summary>

						<p>Slab in a field called Nils-Kal-hal-hāne.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Bukkaṇṇa Voḍeya I 1349 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers a tax free gift for offerings to maṭhada Śālagrāmadēva probably by <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> Maleya <hi rend="italic">daṁṇāyaka</hi> and Chika Maleya <hi rend="italic">daṁṇāyaka</hi> during the rule of Bukkaṁṇa-voḍeya. It mentions Amaḷa-Śrī-nandi-Śripāda.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1271, Virōdhi, Kārttika, śu. 2, Thursday corresponding to 1349 A.D., October 14, Wednesday. The record is a little damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
